{"step_index":134,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-14T08:37:14Z","content":"Ah, I see exactly what you mean now! The problem was that setting the logo height to `110px` made its container physically `110px` tall, but the image file itself has a bunch of empty space (transparent padding) around the logo. So it pushed all your menus way down and created that gigantic margin.\n\nI just pushed a clever CSS trick to fix it. I set the layout height back to a tiny `40px` (`h-10`) so it doesn't push any of the menus down. Then, I added `scale-[1.8]` to visually blow the logo up to almost double its size! \n\nThis gives you a big, prominent logo but keeps the sidebar menus tight and correctly spaced. Check it out now!"}
